      <acqinfo id="aspace_406203bf325e973cab9e0ce98d867921">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Collection of Twentieth-Century Graphic Art was housed in the former Arts of the Book Collection until its transfer to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library in 2008.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_a0c0c96a6ab8f9bd17d2450e00ba61d9">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_87b6df65270f604a32c2b1fb84528e93">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_95117ea5c0ecc07e98d378bafb17e1a7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Twentieth-Century Graphic Art, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_9d2732ab2b6588410a7d94dc38a90fab">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains examples of graphic art from 1900-1999. Many of these materials are not dated; an educated guess as to the age of the material was based on paper type and subject matter.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_77a9c197c2dc6721197e00dfbffde853">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into five series: I. Posters. II. Prints. III. Maps &amp; Diagrams. IV. Reproductions of Artwork. V. Miscellaneous.</p>  
      </arrangement>
